==English==

===Noun===
'''[[last]] [[minute]]'''

# {{idiom}} An arbitrary (non-specific) point in [[time]], too close to a [[deadline]] to [[reasonably]] begin a critical [[task]].
#: ''I like to do everything at the '''last minute'''. It does tend to make me late for things, though.''

===Adjective===
'''[[last]] [[minute]]'''

# {{idiom}} Very close to a deadline.
#: ''All that '''last minute''' revision really payed off in the exam!''